            make.arrow                                      make.arrow




            with making the north arrow are:
                 
                 -w (window/region) [data=d][map plot=p]
                 -p (pen) [plotter pen location=value]
                 -j (justify) [center=c][right=r][left=l]
                 -x (horizontal coordinate) [right=>[centimeter=value]]
                                          [left=<[centimeter=value]]
                                          [center=|[centimeter=value]]
                 -y (vertical coordinate) [top=>[centimeter=value]]
                                        [bottom=<[centimeter=value]]
                                        [center=|[centimeter=value]]
                 -f (font/symbol) [font=-alphanumeric]
                 -s (size) [centimeter=value]
                 -r (rotate) [degrees=value]
                 -t (text)
                 [text string]
                 . (end text)
            
            EXAMPLE
            The file misc/northarrow will draw a north arrow symbol,
            which is identified as symbol 79 on the ksym2 font, rotated
            90 degrees, at 20 cm in x and 5.5 cm in y away from the
            lower left corner of the data window.  It will be drawn with
            the pen in position one on the plotter .75 cm high.
            
                 legend -m map.def -o ovm/n.arrow << EOF
                 -w d
                 -j l
                 -x 20.0
                 -y 5.5
                 -f -ksym2
                 -p 1
                 -s 0.75
                 -r 90
                 -t
                 O              # ascii character for symbol 79
                 .
                 EOF
            
            NOTE
            If only one map element will be drawn on the map
            composition, the default selection for the file name is
            recommended for use.
            
            The delete key will abort the make.arrow command.
            
